
    Priyanka Chopra: US writer sorry for 'scam artist' comment

        

    
        
                
                Image copyright
                 Reuters
                
            
            
            Image caption
                
                    Ms Chopra (R) and Mr Jonas are in Udaipur for another big wedding
                
            A US journalist has apologised after writing that Bollywood actress Priyanka Chopra was a "scam artist" who had trapped US singer Nick Jonas into marrying her to further her career.Mariah Smith said she took "full responsibility for what I wrote, and I was wrong. I am truly sorry".The article in The Cut, a New York-based website, has since been taken down.Many Indians had jumped to Ms Chopra's defence and accused The Cut of racism.However Ms Smith said she did not "condone racism, xenophobia, or sexism".
    
        

    
        
